snippet: A Florida state attorney only learned this week about a 2012 report of sexual battery involving the Seminoles’ quarterback, Jameis Winston, who is a Heisman Trophy contender.
abstract: Florida state attorney William N Meggs says he has only recently learned about 2012 report of sexual battery involving Florida State University quarterback Jameis Winston; admits he does not understand how charge has gone without investigation for so long, but pledges to get to bottom of issue.
lead_paragraph: A Florida state attorney only learned this week about a 2012 report of sexual battery involving the Seminoles’ quarterback, Jameis Winston, who is a Heisman Trophy contender.

headline.main: Prosecutor Plans to Interview F.S.U. Quarterback’s Accuser
headline.print_headline: Prosecutor Plans to Interview F.S.U. Quarterback’s Accuser
